HIV/AIDS: China ta ba da rahoton karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na sababbin cututtuka
Kasar Sin ta ce yawan mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya karu da kashi 14 cikin 100.
Hukumomin lafiya sun ce an kashe fiye da mutane 820,000 a ƙasar.
An samu wasu sabbin mutane 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kawai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun kasance ta hanyar jima'i kuma sun nuna canji daga shekarun baya.
A wasu wurare a ƙasar Sin, cutar HIV tana yaduwa da sauri sakamakon ƙarin jini.
Amma, adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan sifili, in ji hukumomin kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, yawan mutanen da ke rayuwa da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000 a kowace shekara.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i abu ne mai gaggawa a cikin al'ummar kasar Sin ta HIV.
An yi watsi da jima'i a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma ana ganin nuna bambanci ga masu cutar da jima'i da kuma jima'i da maza da mata a kasar.
Domin ra'ayin da mutanen ƙasar suke da shi, an yi la'akari da cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza za su auri mata.
Yawancin cututtukan da ke faruwa a cikin wannan yanayin sun faru ne saboda rashin kariya ta jima'i a cikin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samun maganin HIV a ko'ina a duniya a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance matsalar.
