Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi nuni a ranar Laraba da cewa jaridar China Daily ta biya wani karin kuɗi a cikin Des Moines Register - jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a jihar Iowa - bayan ta zargi kasar Sin da kokarin shiga cikin zaben Amurka na shida, abin da kasar Sin ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi na cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka fada wa Reuters shine sabon mataki na kara karuwar yakin neman zabe daga Washington da nufin matsa lamba a kasar Sin.
Ko da yake yana da kyau gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje su yi amfani da talla don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin faɗaɗa yaƙin kasuwanci da ke ƙara haraji a kan shigo da kayayyakin da suke shigowa da su.
An tsara harajin da kasar Sin ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya don kaiwa masu fitar da kaya a jihohi kamar Iowa da ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump hari, a cewar masana na kasar Sin da Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kuma kamfanoni lahani.
Branstad ya rubuta a wata muhawara a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register a ranar Lahadi cewa, "yanzu kasar Sin tana ƙara yawan zalunci ta wajen buga tallan da ke nuna cewa muna son mu yi wa mutane laifi".
